description: Many recent shelter promotions have focused on free adoptions and overcrowding at our county shelters. It's true- the shelter is full...and we are so full that the value for the amazing animals in the shelter's care has literally been reduced to zero dollars.    However, I will say that the tagline that we "HAVE to adopt 300 big dogs out NOW" makes me uneasy...    A decision to adopt should be a thoug ... htful one. It should not be hastened by guilt or a sense that if we adopt out 300 animals, all will be well. Because I promise you from years of volunteer experience that 300 more animals will be at the shelter within a few weeks. Until we fix the root of the problem, the problem will not go away: we can't fix a hemorrhage with a bandaid. Until we educate on the importance of adopting, spaying/neutering, and treating animals as family, our community will continue to hemorrhage animals into our shelters.     I know that many people respond to desperate pleas such as these, but I also know that some people find this information and this constant barrage of "HELP US NOW!!" to be overwhelming.     By all means- PLEASE, help spread the word. Tell your friends and family about how crowded the shelters are. Encourage people to adopt. Encourage people to become involved- volunteering and fostering is so rewarding and so needed!     But please, be thoughtful with your decision to adopt.     Adopt for love. Adopt for life. Because a pet is forever.  <3   See More
